omRsaPrivateKey() throws Exception {\\n+        KeyPairGenerator generator = KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\\\"RSA\\\");\\n+        generator.initialize(1024);\\n+        KeyPair keyPair = generator.generateKeyPair();\\n+\\n+        PublicKey derived = PublicKeyDeriver.derivePublicKey(keyPair.getPrivate());\\n+\\n+        assertThat(derived.getAlgorithm()).isEqualTo(\\\"RSA\\\");\\n+        assertThat(derived.getEncoded()).containsExactly(keyPair.getPublic().getEncoded());\\n+    }\\n+\\n+    private static final class TestOption implements KOption {\\n+        private final KOptionInfo optionInfo;\\n+\\n+        private TestOption(String name, KOptionType type) {\\n+            this.optionInfo = new KOptionInfo(name, \\\"Test option \\\" + name, type);\\n+        }\\n+\\n+        @Override\\n+        public KOptionInfo getOptionInfo() {\\n+            return optionInfo;\\n+        }\\n     }\\n }\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777410340637}}\n29426:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating command options**\\n\\nI need to think about using commands like Bash and grep, but I notice there's an issue with compiling or testing. Maybe I should check for differences in code with `git diff`. It feels like I’m on the right track to troubleshoot this situation by using the right commands to understand what’s going wrong and figure out how to proceed effectively. I'll keep exploring the best options to resolve this!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0ca578cf224ecac10169f12121c428819c93946080470a6424\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp8SEjk2TxuJ7St8SslS7ViMl27fSM23C6xUqdXDEcC2FkY0xHoeYe5d5EkkPJT6U3fi8PfRNNsBRNq1jG-BGsbiHl-f8d2jLR5TdL0bdtchhzk8nEyuorWG2eO5V0adQtoyasfCfCpUt332-rQCTs1WZ51DYrBRpuFTOxgW22vSz5SuKE1MRyNyJ23IjVveSxXxn6UiATdNDcNGnHSi3JdkDaZDUfXOiUtFRRjjNX4OChmIZTa8KRU1tf9tyKlzQhZRfNg1q4SPbTQTHFqKZTmfbZGG_CUIjVo